GIDDY'S AI SUPPORT AGENT

The Challenge
An online cake shop, Giddy's, required a virtual assistant capable of handling customer inquiries for cakes, cupcakes, and muffins, scheduling appointments while managing delivery logistics for only two counties in Kenya: Homa Bay and Kisumu.

The Solution
I architected an n8n-based AI Agent that integrates natural language processing with hard-coded operational logic. This prevents "Zone 3" model collapse by using a JavaScript Code Tool to validate delivery locations before any data is committed to the database.

📂 Technical Architecture
1. Trigger & Brain
Trigger: Webhook / Chat Message received.

AI Model: OpenAI (GPT-4o).

Memory Node: Window Buffer Memory (Configured to retain the last 5 interactions to ensure context—like cake flavor—is not lost during the checkout flow).

2. The Action Layer (Tools)
The agent is equipped with three primary tools to move from "chatting" to "doing":

A. The Logistics Validator (JavaScript Code Tool)
To ensure the AI doesn't promise deliveries to unsupported regions, I implemented a logic gate.

